<p class="dfe-adminui-text-muted"><small>Note: For info (blue) progress bars, use black text (#000) when progress is less than 50%, and white text (#fff) when progress is 50% or greater, to ensure accessibility.</small></p>

<h2>Text colour logic</h2>
<p>
    The text colour should adapt based on the progress percentage to ensure readability:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>If progress ≥ 50%: Use white text (#fff) as the center (50%) is within the coloured bar</li>
    <li>If progress &lt; 50%: Use black text (#000) as the center is on the grey background</li>
</li>
</ul>

<h2>Usage guidelines</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Use progress bars to show completion status or progress toward a goal</li>
    <li>Always include percentage text for clarity</li>
    <li>Use appropriate colour coding:
        <ul>
            <li>Green (success) for high completion (≥75%)</li>
            <li>Amber (warning) for medium completion (50-74%)</li>
            <li>Red (danger) for low completion (&lt;50%)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Ensure text is always readable by adjusting colour based on progress percentage</li>
    <li>Use a height of 30px for standard progress bars</li>
    <li>Include proper ARIA attributes for accessibility</li>
</ul>

<h2>Accessibility</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Always include <code>role="progressbar"</code></li>
    <li>Set <code>aria-valuenow</code> to the current progress value</li>
    <li>Set <code>aria-valuemin="0"</code> and <code>aria-valuemax="100"</code></li>
    <li>Ensure text contrast meets WCAG requirements</li>
    <li>Use semantic HTML structure</li>
</ul>

<h2>Code example</h2>
<pre><code>@{
    var progress = 75; // percentage
    var progressBarClass = progress >= 75 ? "bg-success" : progress >= 50 ? "bg-warning" : "bg-danger";
    var textColor = progress >= 50 ? "#fff" : "#000";
}
&lt;div class="progress" style="height: 30px; position: relative; background-color: #e9ecef; width: 100%;"&gt;
    &lt;div class="progress-bar @progressBarClass" 
         role="progressbar" 
         style="width: @progress% !important; min-width: 0 !important; position: relative;"
         aria-valuenow="@progress" 
         aria-valuemin="0" 
         aria-valuemax="100"&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;span style="position: absolute; left: 50%; top: 50%; transform: translate(-50%, -50%); font-weight: bold; white-space: nowrap; pointer-events: none; z-index: 2; color: @textColor;"&gt;
        @progress%
    &lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>
